import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['budgetYear'])]
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    data['budgetYear'] = data['budgetYear'].dt.year
    data['forecastYear'] = data['forecastYear'].dt.year
    pivot = data.pivot_table(index='budgetYear', columns='forecastYear', values='value')
    sns.heatmap(pivot, cmap='YlGnBu', annot=True, fmt=".2f", linewidths=.5)
    plt.xlabel('forecastYear')
    plt.ylabel('budgetYear')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of value across budgetYear and forecastYear?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['budgetYear'])]
    data['budgetYear'] = data['budgetYear'].dt.strftime('%Y')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.axhline(y=data['value'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average value')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the average value for each budgetYear?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Budget Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Value')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['budgetYear'])]
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    data['budgetYear'] = data['budgetYear'].dt.year
    data['forecastYear'] = data['forecastYear'].dt.year
    data = data.pivot_table(index='forecastYear', columns='budgetYear', values='abs_diff')
    ax = sns.heatmap(data, cmap='YlGnBu', annot=True, fmt=".2f", linewidths=.5, cbar_kws={'label': 'abs_diff'})
    ax.set_xlabel('budgetYear')
    ax.set_ylabel('forecastYear')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of abs_diff across budgetYear and forecastYear?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
